			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Do not underestimate this spell whatsoever. I have recently begun this spell for crowd control.<BR>
<BR>
The trick is to use root like an enchanter uses &quot;mez&quot;. Cast it on extra mobs (works better on non-casters) and forget em. As long as no one attacks the mob your root will hold a very long time. An even better tactic is to root em and DOT em since the DOT's don't seem to effect the root at all.<BR>
<BR>
The only trick is to make sure your party is aware of what is going on. Make em back away from the rooted mob to move the battle out of its reach.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
